="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">National Crime Recording Standards (NCRS) and National Standards for Incident Recording (NSIR) audits are undertaken regularly and reported to Chief Officers and my Office both directly and through an Executive Perfo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rmance Summary. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Audit results across 2013 from Gloucestershire show that 91% of crimes that should be recorded are recorded. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This figure however fluctuates across the different crime categories, with 96% of acquisitive crimes recorded and 88% of violent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> crimes recorded. As for the classification of crimes, Gloucestershire currently has upwards of 95% of offences categorised correctly.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> This is due in the most part to the way that the Constabulary has control of the recording of crimes within the Force Cr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ime Validation &amp; Evaluation Unit.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The audit process was changed early in 2013 from solely looking at thematic (one crime type at a time) to a regular overall audit.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> 400 incidents are looked at every month, split by crime types. Three things are measured:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Incident to crime (called 'Investigation 1' as it’s the 1st test in the Home Office audit guide), this measures every incident to see if a crime has been identified correctly and timely.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Criming rate - this looks at number of crimes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">identified in the incidents (by the Force Information Auditor as per guidelines) and compares it to the number actually recorded.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">NSIR - has the incident been given the correct closure code.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This review and change in practice and regular reporting gives</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> me confidence in the crime statistics for Gloucestershire to the extent indicated above.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>